State of Connecticut v. Nunzio Parente (10019)

Norcott, Lavery and Heiman, Js.

Argued January 7 decision released January 28, 1992 Milo J. Altschuler, for the appellant (defendant). Carolyn K. Longstreth, assistant state’s attorney, with whom were Francis McQuade, assistant state’s attorney, and, on the brief, Mary Galvin, state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
